<title>MEXICO: Banco de Mexico assigns first direct Cetes sale.</title>
<headline>Banco de Mexico assigns first direct Cetes sale.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-05-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Banco de Mexico on Tuesday assigned the first of three direct Cetes sales, which it was combining with six repurchase agreements to drain a total of 4.994 billion pesos from the secondary market, dealers said.</p>
<p>The Cetes sales were offered or assigned as follows:</p>
<p>    AMOUNT     TERM	 AVERAGE RATE</p>
<p>    500 million    331 days   23.14 pct</p>
<p>    500 million    176 days</p>
<p>    500 million     86 days</p>
<p>The terms and maturities of the repurchase agreements were offered as follows:</p>
<p>    600 million     51 days</p>
<p>    600 million     45 days</p>
<p>    700 million     37 days</p>
<p>    700 million     23 days</p>
<p>    600 million     16 days</p>
<p>    294 million	1 day</p>
<p>*Amounts in pesos</p>
<p>(( --Mexico City newsroom +525 728-9559))</p>
